Title: Creates a special on-premises license for certain properties
Summary: Creates a special on-premises license for properties which are located within a designated industrial or economic zoning district, occupy not less than twenty thousand square feet of floor area, and are utilized for the purpose of hosting entertainment or cultural, social, or community events.
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the alcoholic beverage control law, in relation to creating a special on-premises license for certain properties
